## 2026-03-27 - No conflict detection for concurrent edits — if a token is modified on the server while the editor is open, saving silently overwrites the server version
- Added pre-save conflict detection to TokenEditor: when saving (PATCH), the editor re-fetches the current server state and compares it (via `JSON.stringify`) to the snapshot captured on initial load. If they differ, a ConfirmModal is shown: "Token modified on server — overwrite?" If the user confirms, `handleSave(true)` is called with `forceOverwrite=true` to skip the check. If the conflict check fetch fails (network error), save proceeds normally to avoid blocking the user.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/TokenEditor.tsx` ~L171 (new state/ref), ~L218 (snapshot capture), ~L397 (conflict check in handleSave), ~L1332 (conflict ConfirmModal in JSX)
